    <item>
      <title>Best Budget Build Tools for a First Van Conversion</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/best-of/budget-build-tools/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/best-of/budget-build-tools/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;You do not need a garage full of tools for a strong first build. You need a small set of reliable tools and a clear sequence.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;callout-shortcode&#34;&gt;&#xA;  &lt;p class=&#34;callout-title&#34;&gt;Quick Answer&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;  &lt;div class=&#34;callout-body&#34;&gt;Buy fewer tools but buy reliable core tools: drill/driver, jigsaw, rivnut tool, crimper, torque wrench, and safety gear.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;We’re keeping this high-level—no wiring instructions here. For installs, follow manufacturer guidance or work with a qualified installer.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Bluetti Charger 1 Alternator Charger Review</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/gear/bluetti-charger-1-alternator-charger-review/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/gear/bluetti-charger-1-alternator-charger-review/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Alternator charging can fix one of the biggest van life pain points: cloudy-day power shortfalls.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;my-4 rounded-md border p-3 text-sm opacity-90&#34;&gt;Disclosure: Some links may be affiliate links. If you buy, we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;span class=&#34;inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md px-4 py-2 font-semibold shadow-sm border border-transparent bg-neutral-900 text-white hover:bg-neutral-700 opacity-60 cursor-not-allowed&#34; aria-disabled=&#34;true&#34;&gt;Link coming soon&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Pros&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;pros&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#pros&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Improves recharge speed while driving.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Makes portable station setups more practical for full-timers.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Better uptime for remote workers.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Cons&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;cons&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#cons&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Install complexity is higher than plug-and-play solutions.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Requires confidence in wiring and fuse planning.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Value depends heavily on driving frequency.&#xA;We’re keeping this high-level—no wiring instructions here. For installs, follow manufacturer guidance or work with a qualified installer.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Who It’s For&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;who-its-for&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#who-its-for&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;People who drive regularly and need dependable charge recovery.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Van lifers pairing portable stations with mobile work.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Still Worth It?&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;still-worth-it&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#still-worth-it&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Yes for frequent drivers. If you stay parked for long periods, prioritize solar and load reduction first.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>How Much Solar Do You Need in a Van?</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/how-much-solar-do-you-need-in-a-van/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/how-much-solar-do-you-need-in-a-van/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Most people should estimate usage first, then choose solar. Start with a daily load list in watt-hours.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Quick Sizing Rule&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;quick-sizing-rule&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#quick-sizing-rule&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Light use: 200W&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Moderate daily use: 300W-400W&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Heavy remote work + fridge: 500W+&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Then match battery capacity to at least one day of use.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>MaxxAir MaxxFan Deluxe 7500 Review</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/gear/maxxair-maxxfan-deluxe-7500k-review/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/gear/maxxair-maxxfan-deluxe-7500k-review/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;For many full-time van lifers, a quality roof fan is one of the highest ROI upgrades.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;my-4 rounded-md border p-3 text-sm opacity-90&#34;&gt;Disclosure: Some links may be affiliate links. If you buy, we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;span class=&#34;inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md px-4 py-2 font-semibold shadow-sm border border-transparent bg-neutral-900 text-white hover:bg-neutral-700 opacity-60 cursor-not-allowed&#34; aria-disabled=&#34;true&#34;&gt;Link coming soon&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Pros&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;pros&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#pros&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Reliable airflow and strong comfort improvements.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Remote operation is useful during daily routines.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Better rain usability than basic fan models.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Cons&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;cons&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#cons&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;More expensive than entry-level alternatives.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Install quality matters; poor sealing causes long-term headaches.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Who It’s For&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;who-its-for&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#who-its-for&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Full-time or frequent van users in varied climates.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Builders prioritizing sleep and moisture control.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Still Worth It?&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;still-worth-it&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#still-worth-it&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Yes. It remains one of the safest default choices in this category.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Radiant Composite Insulation &#43; Polyiso for Van Builds</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/gear/radiant-technology-composite-insulation-plus-polyiso-guide/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/gear/radiant-technology-composite-insulation-plus-polyiso-guide/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Insulation choices affect comfort, condensation risk, and long-term build durability.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&lt;div class=&#34;my-4 rounded-md border p-3 text-sm opacity-90&#34;&gt;Disclosure: Some links may be affiliate links. If you buy, we may earn a commission at no extra cost to you.&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;span class=&#34;inline-flex items-center justify-center rounded-md px-4 py-2 font-semibold shadow-sm border border-transparent bg-neutral-900 text-white hover:bg-neutral-700 opacity-60 cursor-not-allowed&#34; aria-disabled=&#34;true&#34;&gt;Link coming soon&lt;/span&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Pros&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;pros&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#pros&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Layered approach can improve thermal performance in mixed climates.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Materials are generally accessible and budget-scalable.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Good fit for phased DIY builds.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Cons&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;cons&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#cons&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Install complexity around curves and thermal bridging.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Results depend heavily on air sealing quality.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Who It’s For&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;who-its-for&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#who-its-for&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;DIY builders prioritizing practical comfort over luxury finishes.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;People converting in variable climate conditions.&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Still Worth It?&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;still-worth-it&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#still-worth-it&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Yes, when executed carefully. Material choice alone does not fix poor install strategy.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Tools You’ll Actually Use in a First Build</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/tools-youll-actually-use-in-a-first-build/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/tools-youll-actually-use-in-a-first-build/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;The fastest way to overspend on a build is buying every tool recommended online.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Buy First&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;buy-first&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#buy-first&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Drill/driver combo&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Jigsaw + quality blades&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Crimper + multimeter&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;PPE and measuring tools&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Borrow or Rent&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;borrow-or-rent&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#borrow-or-rent&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;ul&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Specialty saws&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;li&gt;Rare-use heavy tools&lt;/li&gt;&#xA;&lt;/ul&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Why This Matters&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;why-this-matters&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#why-this-matters&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;Tool quality affects safety and finish quality, but tool count does not.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
    <item>
      <title>Ventilation Mistakes New Van Lifers Make</title>
      <link>http://localhost:1313/blog/ventilation-mistakes-new-van-lifers-make/</link>
      <pubDate>Sat, 21 Feb 2026 00:00:00 +0000</pubDate>
      
      <guid>http://localhost:1313/blog/ventilation-mistakes-new-van-lifers-make/</guid>
      <description>&lt;p&gt;Bad airflow causes more daily frustration than most first-time builders expect.&lt;/p&gt;&#xA;&#xA;&lt;h2 class=&#34;relative group&#34;&gt;Mistake 1: No Crossflow Plan&#xA;    &lt;div id=&#34;mistake-1-no-crossflow-plan&#34; class=&#34;anchor&#34;&gt;&lt;/div&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;    &lt;span&#xA;        class=&#34;absolute top-0 w-6 transition-opacity opacity-0 -start-6 not-prose group-hover:opacity-100 select-none&#34;&gt;&#xA;        &lt;a class=&#34;text-primary-300 dark:text-neutral-700 !no-underline&#34; href=&#34;#mistake-1-no-crossflow-plan&#34; aria-label=&#34;Anchor&#34;&gt;#&lt;/a&gt;&#xA;    &lt;/span&gt;&#xA;    &#xA;&lt;/h2&gt;&#xA;&lt;p&gt;A roof fan alone is not enough. Pair extraction with side-window intake.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
      
    </item>
    
